Package: sticky-notes
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: xdg-utils
Description: desktop sticky notes with rich text and to-do lists
 Sticky Notes keeps small rich-text notes on your desktop. It runs as a
 background service with a status-notifier tray icon, restores your notes at
 login, and supports bold/italic/underline, fonts, colours, alignment, and
 inline checkable to-do items.
 .
 Notes are stored locally in SQLite and can be exported, imported, or emailed
 to yourself as a backup.
